undefined at \(x=B\) where
$BR
\(B=\) \{ans_rule(5)\} 
EOT
$ans = 0;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is concave up (type in CU) or concave down (type in CD).
$BR
 \( (-\infty, B) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "CD";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( (B,\infty) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
